^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Actually no you did not hope. You were just unlucky. Before we get to the bidding, two very important principles on defense. When playing third hand high, always play the lowest in your honor sequence. It tells partner important information. When Kerrie plays the Ace I have no idea who has the King or Queen. But when she plays the Queen and it wins, I know she has the Ace and King. That it is why it is crucial to play the lowest in your sequence as third hand.|
