^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Excellent Kerrie :). Since Kerrie did a squeeze, lets talk about the technique. She has 11 sure tricks 5 hearts 3 clubs 2 spades and a diamond. To squeeze for a 12th trick she has to lose her tricks early. In this case, since she is trying for 12 tricks she must lose one trick. And since she has to lose the Ace of hearts, losing one trick is easy. Her most likely squeeze is in clubs and diamonds. If one person has both the King and Queen of diamonds plus 4 clubs, then it works. |
PG| ***** 72 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, all Kerrie needs to do is keep track of clubs. She just runs her tricks and watches for any club discards. She knows there are six out against her, so as long as she keeps track of how many are played, she knows if the squeeze worked or not. Squeezes do not require a huge amount of brain power. Usually you only need to keep track of one, or at most two, suits.|
